main event: An oval-shaped object, the size of a propeller-driven aircraft, was observed on ground-radar in Clear Lake, South Dakota.
interesting points: The object was detected by ground-radar at a distance of 7 to 10 miles and ranging from 15,000 to 18,000 feet., The observation lasted for one hour., The object was still visible after being observed visually and through binoculars., The object exhibited no maneuvers during the observation., The case has been referred to Project Blue Book for further evaluation.
witness description: No confirmed witnesses mentioned, observation was through ground-radar.
